Code Challenges
This repository contains solutions for three coding challenges. These programs can be tested using a web browser's developer console. Below are detailed instructions and code samples for each challenge.

Table of Contents
Student Grade Generator
Speed Detector
Net Salary Calculator


1.Student Grade Generator
Description
This program calculates the grade based on the input marks. The grades are assigned as follows:

A: Marks > 79
B: Marks between 60 and 79
C: Marks between 50 and 59
D: Marks between 40 and 49
E: Marks below 40
Code
javascript
Copy code
function getGrade(marks) {
  if (marks >= 80) return 'A';
  if (marks >= 60) return 'B';
  if (marks >= 50) return 'C';
  if (marks >= 40) return 'D';
  return 'E';
}

// Example testing
let marks = 85; // Change this value to test
console.log('Grade:', getGrade(marks));
Testing
Open your browser (e.g., Chrome).
Press F12 or Ctrl+Shift+I to open the Developer Tools.
Go to the Console tab.
Paste and run the code above.
Observe the output in the console.


2.Speed Detector
Description
This program checks the speed of a car and calculates demerit points based on the speed limit. If the speed exceeds 70 km/h, for every 5 km/h over the limit, one demerit point is added. If points exceed 12, the license is suspended.

Code
javascript
Copy code
function speedDetector(speed) {
  const speedLimit = 70;
  if (speed < speedLimit) {
    console.log('Ok');
  } else {
    const points = Math.floor((speed - speedLimit) / 5);
    if (points > 12) {
      console.log('License suspended');
    } else {
      console.log('Points:', points);
    }
  }
}

// Example testing
let speed = 85; // Change this value to test
speedDetector(speed);
Testing
Follow the same steps as for the Student Grade Generator to test the code in the browser console.


3.Net Salary Calculator
Description
This program calculates an individual's net salary based on the basic salary and benefits. It takes into account tax, NHIF (National Hospital Insurance Fund), and NSSF (National Social Security Fund) deductions.

Code
javascript
Copy code
function calculateNetSalary(basicSalary, benefits) {
  // Tax calculation logic (example values)
  const taxRate = 0.2; // 20% tax rate
  const nhif = 200; // Example NHIF deduction
  const nssf = 100; // Example NSSF deduction
  const grossSalary = basicSalary + benefits;
  const tax = grossSalary * taxRate;
  const netSalary = grossSalary - tax - nhif - nssf;

  console.log('Gross Salary:', grossSalary);
  console.log('Tax:', tax);
  console.log('NHIF:', nhif);
  console.log('NSSF:', nssf);
  console.log('Net Salary:', netSalary);
}

// Example testing
let basicSalary = 5000; // Change this value to test
let benefits = 1000; // Change this value to test
calculateNetSalary(basicSalary, benefits);
Testing
Follow the same steps as for the previous challenges to test the code in the browser console.
